.config/opencode/commands

# Orphaned compound-engineering skills. They used to be fetched into
# ~/.agents/skills/ by the dotagents `[[skills]] name = "*"` wildcard entry;
# that entry is gone, because the plugin is now installed natively per agent
# (see the compound-engineering section in AGENTS.md). dotagents does NOT prune
# skill directories it no longer declares — its lock file drops them but the
# dirs stay, and its `sync` cannot run here at all (the chezmoi-managed
# ~/.agents/agents.toml is 0400, so sync's rewrite of it EACCESes). Left behind,
# every ce-* skill would load TWICE: once as a stale directory here and once
# from the plugin.
#
# Safe: these `ce-*` / `lfg` patterns match neither the external skills deployed
# there (`playwright-cli`, `improve`) nor the locally-authored chezmoi-managed
# skills under dot_agents/skills/<name>/ (`daily-report`); dotagents will never
# re-create the ce-* dirs now that the wildcard entry is gone.
.agents/skills/ce-*
.agents/skills/lfg
